The **Universal Gizmo** is a transform widget designed for moving, rotating, and scaling Actors when working in VR mode. 

![](TransformGizmo.png)(w:400)


The elements of the Universal Gizmo are colored red, green, and blue representing the X, Y, and Z axes, respectively. 

| Action | Manipulator | Usage |
| --- | --- | --- |
| **Translate** | ![](Translate.png)(w:300) | Aim the controller at one of the translation manipulators and squeeze the **Trigger** halfway to grab it. Move the controller to move the selected Actor(s) along the axis. |
| **Translate Plane** | ![](TranslatePlane.png)(w:300) | Aim the controller at one of the translation plane manipulators and squeeze the **Trigger** halfway to grab it. Move the controller to move the selected Actor(s) along the plane (in 2 axes). |
| **Rotate** | ![](Rotate.png)(w:300) | Aim the controller at one of the rotation manipulators and squeeze the **Trigger** halfway to grab it. Move the controller to rotate the selected Actor(s) around the axis. |
| **Uniform Scale** | ![](UniformScale.png)(w:300) | Aim the controller at the white cube in the center of the gizmo and squeeze the **Trigger** halfway to grab it. Move the controller to scale the selected Actor(s) along all axes uniformly. |
| **Scale** | ![](NonUniformScale.png)(w:300) | Aim the controller at one of the scale manipulators and squeeze the **Trigger** halfway to grab it. Move the controller to scale the selected Actor(s) along the Y-axis. Note that the individual scale manipulators only show if you have set **Local Space** using the [Quick Select Menu](Engine/Editor/VR/QuickSelect).|

